## Step-by-Step Deployment

### Step 1 — Replace the 3 existing files

```
server.js                     ← replace with server.js from this folder
src/schemas/validation.js     ← replace with validation.js from this folder
src/pages/CheckoutPage.jsx    ← replace with CheckoutPage.jsx from this folder
```

### Step 2 — Add the migration script

```
scripts/sync-inventory.js     ← copy sync-inventory.js from this folder
```

### Step 3 — Run the one-time migration

```bash
node scripts/sync-inventory.js
```

This reads all existing products from MongoDB and creates a document
in the `inventories` collection for each one. Run this only once.
After this, the inventories collection stays in sync automatically.

### Step 4 — Deploy

```bash
npm run build
# Railway auto-deploys on git push
```

