## MongoDB Structure After Migration

You will see exactly 3 main data collections in MongoDB Compass / Atlas:

```
stopshop (database)
├── products        ← master catalogue
├── orders          ← every customer order
├── inventories     ← stock management
├── admins          ← admin accounts
├── settings        ← store settings
├── auditlogs       ← audit trail
└── subscribers     ← newsletter
```

---

## What Each Collection Contains

### `products`
Every product the admin creates/edits. Fields:
- `id`, `name`, `price`, `quantity`, `stock`
- `bucket` (category), `subCategory`
- `specs`, `colors`, `sizes`, `sizeStock`
- `image`, `gallery`, `lifestyleImage`, `variantImages`
- `rating`, `mediaType`, `embedCode`

**Auto-updates when:** Admin creates, edits, or deletes a product via the admin panel.

---

### `orders`
Every customer purchase. Fields:
- `orderID` (e.g. `ORD-LX8K2A`)
- `customer.name`, `customer.email`, `customer.address`, `customer.city`, `customer.zip`
- `items[]` — **full product snapshot at time of purchase:**
  - `id`, `name`, `price`, `quantity`
  - `selectedSize` (what size the customer chose)
  - `selectedColor` (what color the customer chose) ← NEW
  - `category` (e.g. Tops) ← NEW
  - `subCategory` (e.g. T-Shirt) ← NEW
- `total`
- `paymentMethod` — one of: `COD`, `ATM Card`, `Bank Transfer`, `Easypaisa`, `JazzCash`
- `status` — `Pending` → `Processing` → `Shipped` → `Delivered`

**Auto-creates when:** A customer completes checkout.

---

### `inventories`
Stock management layer. Fields:
- `productId`, `sku` — links back to `products.id`
- `name`, `category`, `subCategory`, `price`, `image`, `rating`
- `colorVariants[]`, `sizes[]`
- `totalStock` — aggregate across all sizes
- `sizeStock` — `{ S: 10, M: 5, L: 3 }` breakdown
- `status` — `In Stock` / `Low Stock` / `Out of Stock` (auto-computed)
- `lowStockThreshold` — default 5
- `lastRestocked`, `lastSold`, `lastAdminEdit`
- `movements[]` — rolling 100-entry history of stock changes:
  - `type`: `INITIAL | RESTOCK | SALE | ADMIN_UPDATE`
  - `quantityDelta`: `+10` (restock) or `-2` (sale)
  - `previousStock`, `newStock`
  - `note` — human-readable description
  - `triggeredBy`: `admin` or `customer`
  - `orderId` — links to the order that triggered the sale

**Auto-updates when:**
- Admin creates/edits/deletes a product → inventory syncs immediately
- Customer buys a product → stock decrements + SALE movement logged
- Admin edits quantity in Inventory page → syncs to both collections

